Why so many lamps? Well, because when I get an idea I never want to make one piece, my brain immediately goes to “Let's make 10 or 100 of these, I want 100 hanging on a large wall altogether.” So when I started making 10, but finished five, I called it done, I needed to move onto other work for the show.  These four are hanging in the show, plus another. They're framed, varnished and 11x14”, you can see them on my website and in person till May 18th @sacstateunion gallery M-F 10:30-3:30pm and W-TH 5-8pm.

Do you like artwork signed on the front or the back? I’m team front from the perspective of collector and artist, I even love a ginormous bold signature when it fits the style. I typically sign mine on the front and back, the back will have year, medium, name printed, signed and then I have little shorthand about varnish or if I’ve prepped a panel. So some panels with have a scrawled note of GAC100 because then I know I prepped that panel months ago, I think I’ll remember and I DO NOT 😆

Going to work on the left painting today. The right already was finished and off to its new home. The finished size will be around 52x54”. Our car of 16 years died, a Toyota Highlander which could fit a 48” wide painting maximum and up to about 72” long. But our new car fits 48” wide flat and according to my measurements 54” diagonal 🎉🎉🎉👩🏻‍🎨 Not sure how long but longer than the Highlander. This is exciting AND it’s a plug-in hybrid. We went with a Pacifica. Now I can happily deliver more artwork around town:)

How are we doing this week? I'll be honest, Summer isn't my favorite season. The heat and lack of routine, I'm struggling with my focus. When I'm struggling with focus, I'm not getting in a flow with my art making, which is my fuel! I suppose I love deep work and summer is a bit of an antithesis to that quiet deep work. Anyone else struggle with this? And to be honest I feel like a bit of an A-hole for disliking summer 😆
